GOGO Hilda Maaroganye was overjoyed when she finally received a house 10 years ago.But ever since the strange rat moved in last year, her life has become hell.The 75-year-old gogo said the rat likes to watch TV with her &ndash; especially Generations!According to gogo Hilda from Snake Park in Soweto, the strange rodent refuses to leave her house.She said: &ldquo;The rat appears from nowhere to watch TV with me, especially when Generations is showing.&ldquo; I tried to hit it with a broom last year, but I ended up on the ground. I broke my leg because of it and now I have to use crutches,&rdquo; said the sad gogo.&ldquo;I tried to use rat poison and glue to kill it, but the rat is still around.&rdquo;She said she even hired a pest control company to deal with the evil creature, but they couldn&rsquo;t find it.&ldquo;My last hope was a rat trap, but it wouldn&rsquo;t go in. I&rsquo;m running out of ideas and I need help before this thing kills me.Traditional healer Mahlinza Dlamini from Vosloorus, Ekurhuleni, said the incident was a familiar one.&ldquo;In most cases, the rat is sent by evil or jealous people who don&rsquo;t want to see their victim happy. &ldquo;The gogo should consult a sangoma to help her get rid of the rat by casting a spell.&rdquo;